Blocks.Text: Almost in desperation She appealed, "Will you meet
me at the gate, four o'clock tomorrow?" "Why?" he
enguired, combing his thick, tawny hair. "To bring
me up for tea, of course. I just thought." "I'll see,"
he told her, and suddenly seized has in an embrace
which really hurt. "Without your ring it's just like
kissing somebody else's girl," he decided wickedly,
and kissed hes again, Somewhat statled to
received a sherp Slap for his pains.
